lor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 26\n| Title               = The Thing and the Absent-Minded Inventor\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|12|15}}\n| ShortSummary        = <small>'''Note:''' This episode aired as part of ''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo''</small>\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n|}\n\n==The New Fred and Barney Show==\n{{main|The New Fred and Barney Show}}\nThe \"Fred and Barney\" half of the show consisted of five new 30-minute episodes of ''The New Fred and Barney Show'' combined with reruns of first-season episodes.\n\n===Episodes===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = Physical Fitness Fred\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|9|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Jealous of Wilma and Betty's attraction to famous Hollyrock star [[Clark Gable|Clark Gravel]], Fred goes all out in a training regimen to get himself in shape in order to impress his wife.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Moonlighters\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|9|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = With prices skyrocketing and Mr. Slate reducing their salaries after misinterpreting their request for a raise, Fred and Barney try out various part-time jobs to compensate for their cash loss, in the process attempting to avoid being seen by Mr. Slate in order to keep their pride.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = Fred Goes to the Houndasaurs\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start